-- Romanian Utility Awards Water-Treatment Plant Contract
-- B y   I r i n a   S a v u
-- 2013-03-14T11:09:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-14/romanian-utility-awards-water-treatment-plant-contract.html
The Romanian utility  Nova Apaserv
SA  awarded a construction contract valued at 30.1 million lei
($8.9 million) for water-treatment plants to the Spanish company
Ocide Construccion SA and Aquaterm SRL venture.  The contract includes the construction of sewage-treatment
plants in Flamanzi and Vorona in the northeastern county of
Botosani and was initially valued at 35.4 million lei, according
to a European Union  procurement document . The utility received
three bids for the contract.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Irina Savu in Bucharest at 
 isavu@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  